<%- include('../partials/head') %>
<section class="hero">
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="lead">Last updated <%= year %>. Torama Vote is operated by Torama Technologies.</p>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2 class="h3">What we collect</h2>
  <p><strong>Organisers:</strong> your email address (for passwordless sign-in and election notices), the elections you create, and payment records (handled by Paystack — we never see or store card details).</p>
  <p><strong>Voters:</strong> ballots are anonymous. We store your choice and a random receipt, never linked to your identity. For open-link elections we store a one-way device fingerprint to prevent double-voting. If a platform administrator enables device auditing for fraud investigation, the IP address and browser of open-link votes may be recorded — still not linked to your ballot choice — and this is disclosed here.</p>
  <p>We use a cookie strictly to keep you signed in and to limit one vote per device. We do not use third-party advertising or tracking.</p>
</section>
<section class="card">
  <h2 class="h3">How we use it</h2>
  <p>To run elections, send sign-in links and receipts, process payments, prevent abuse, and keep the service secure. We do not sell your data.</p>
</section>
<section class="card">
  <h2 class="h3">Retention &amp; your rights</h2>
  <p>Election data is retained while your account is active. You can request deletion of your account and elections by contacting us. We comply with the Nigeria Data Protection Act (NDPA) 2023; where applicable, you have rights to access, correct, and delete your personal data.</p>
</section>
<section class="card">
  <h2 class="h3">Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions about privacy? Email <a href="mailto:privacy@torama.money">privacy@torama.money</a>.</p>
</section>
<p class="help" style="text-align:center;">This summary is provided for transparency and is not legal advice. Have it reviewed by counsel before commercial launch.</p>
